etired Catalan professional [[basketball]] player. Standing at 1.98 m (6'6\"), he played at the [[small forward]] position.\n\n==Professional career==\nMargall's number 7 jersey was [[Club Joventut Badalona#Retired numbers|retired by Joventut Badalona]].\n\n==Spain national team==\nMargall earned 187 [[cap (sports)|times]] with the senior [[Spain national basketball team]].\n\n==References==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170912055551/http://www.acb.com/jugador.php?id=ABW ACB Profile] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{Spain Men Basketball Squad 1980 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Spain Men Basketball Squad 1984 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Spain Men Basketball Squad 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Joventut Badalona 1989\u201390 FIBA Kora\u0107 Cup Champions}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Margall, Josep Maria}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:BC Andorra players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:CB Girona players]]\n[[Category:Catalan basketball players]]\n[[Category:Joventut Badalona players]]\n[[Category:Liga ACB players]]\n[[Category:Olympic basketball players of Spain]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in basketball]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Spain]]\n[[Category:People from Maresme]]\n[[Category:Small forwards]]\n[[Category:Spanish men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:1986 FIBA World Championship players]]\n\n\n{{Spain-basketball-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{catalan name|Margall|Tauler}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography \n| name            = Josep Maria Margall\n| image           = \n| width           = \n| caption         = \n| position        = \n| height_ft       = 6\n| height_in       = 6\n| weight_lb       = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1955|03|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place     = [[Calella]], [[Catalonia]]\n| nationality     = Catalan\n| high_school     = \n| college         = \n| draft_y