{"title_page": "Kevin De Bruyne", "text_new": "{{short description|Moroccan  footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Archie plumb\n| image = Kevin De Bruyne 201807091.jpg\n| image_size =220 \n| caption = De Bruyne with [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] during a press conference at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| fullname = Kevin De Bruyne<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |access-date=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|6|28|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_Squadlists.pdf |title=FIFA World Cup Russia 2018: List of players: Belgium |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=3 |date=15 July 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Drongen]], [[Ghent]], Belgium<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/kevin-de-bruyne/ |title=Kevin De Bruyne: Profile |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n| height = 1.81 m<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n| clubnumber = 17\n| youthyears1 = 1997\u20131999\n| youthclubs1 = KVV Drongen\n| youthyears2 = 1999\u20132005\n| youthclubs2 = [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]]\n| youthyears3 = 2005\u20132008\n| youthclubs3 = [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]\n| years1 = 2008\u20132012\n| clubs1 = [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]\n| caps1 = 97\n| goals1 = 16\n| years2 = 2012\u20132014\n| clubs2 = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n| caps2 = 3\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 33\n| goals3 = 10\n| years4 = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs4 = [[VfL Wolfsburg]]\n| caps4 = 51\n| goals4 = 13\n| years5 = 2015\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n| caps5 = 143\n| goals5 = 31<!--No in-game updates. Only adapt the number of caps and goals when the match is over. Thank you.-->\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\u20132009\n| nationalteam1 = [[Belgium national under-18 football team|Belgium U18]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 7\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalteam2 = [[Belgium national under-19 football team|Belgium U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 10\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2010\u20132011\n| nationalteam3 = [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 2\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2010\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 74<!--Three of his matches with the Belgium national football team are not official according to FIFA rules. Please also adjust the \"ntupdate\" parameter below, by typing the time you adapted the number of caps. Thank you.-->\n| nationalgoals4 = 19\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|BEL}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|3rd|[[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 Russia]]|}}\n| club-update = 15:52, 2 April 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 19 November 2019\n}}\n'''Kevin De Bruyne''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8k\u025bv\u026an d\u0259 \u02c8br\u0153yn\u0259}}; born 28 June 1991) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian national team]]. Recognised for his passing, dribbling, tackling and shooting ability, his playing style has frequently led to the media, coaches, and colleagues ranking him among the best players in the world,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/kevin-de-bruyne-as-good-lionel-messi-cristiano-ronaldo-manchester-city-real-madrid-barcelona-a8045706.html |title=Kevin de Bruyne can become as good as Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo, says Roberto Martinez |newspaper=The Independent |first=Luke |last=Brown |date=9 November 2017 |access-date=16 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.squawka.com/news/pep-guardiola-calls-kevin-de-bruyne-the-best-player-in-europe-bar-one/999940|title=Pep Guardiola calls Kevin De Bruyne \"the best player in Europe bar one\" |publisher=Squawka |first=Cady |last=Siregar |date=16 October 2017 |access-date=16 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/manchester-city/story/3264836/kevin-de-bruyne-best-player-in-the-premier-league-at-the-moment-eden-hazard|title=Kevin De Bruyne best player in Premier League at the moment \u2013 Eden Hazard |date=10 November 2017 |website=ESPN FC |first=Ian |last=Holyman |access-date=16 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41623610 |title=Hughes praises 'best player' in league De Bruyne |date=14 October 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=16 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Bayern Munich boss Heynckes: \"I would give De Bruyne the shirt off my back\" |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/jupp-heynckes-would-give-kevin-de-bruyne-shirt-off-my-back/2eqyxx2j3vqi1dt7leiauui4j |website=goal.com |first=Nicholas |last=McGee |date=15 January 2018 |access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref> and he has often been described as a \"complete\" footballer.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pep Guardiola and Antonio Conte laud Kevin De Bruyne for being the perfect 'complete' player after masterclass |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-perfect-complete-guardiola-conte-reaction-a7976051.html |work=The Independent |first=Miguel |last=Delaney |date=30 September 2017 |access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Where would Manchester City be without Kevin De Bruyne, the most complete player in the Premier League? |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-goals-highlights-most-complete-player-premier-league-a7976031.html |work=The Independent |first=Jack |last=Pitt-Brooke |date=30 September 2017 |access-date=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=FourFourTwo's 100 Best Football Players in the World 2017: No.5, Kevin De Bruyne |quote=The world's most complete midfielder is dropping jaws with his defence-splitting brilliance \u2013 and setting himself on the path to superstardom |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/fourfourtwos-100-best-football-players-world-2017-no5-kevin-de-bruyne#s5xCu64wy6YVu6Yu.99 |work=Talksport |date=15 December 2017 |accessdate=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne began his career at [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]], where he was a regular player when they won the [[2010\u201311 Belgian Pro League]]. In 2012, he joined English club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], where he was used sparingly and then loaned to [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]]. He signed with [[VfL Wolfsburg|Wolfsburg]] for \u00a318 million in 2014, and in 2015 he was named [[Footballer of the Year in Germany]].<ref name=\"Sporza\">{{cite web|url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/buitenland/Duitsland/1.2400701 |title=De Bruyne is Speler van het Jaar volgens Duitse Journalisten |language=nl |date=26 July 2015 |accessdate=26 July 2015 |work=[[Sporza]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716195857/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/buitenland/Duitsland/1.2400701 |archivedate=16 July 2016 |df= }}</ref> Later that year, he joined Manchester City for a club record \u00a354 million. In five seasons with City, De Bruyne has appeared in over 200 matches and won two Premier League titles, four [[EFL Cup|League Cups]] and one [[FA Cup]]. He had a significant role in City's quest to become the first Premier League team to [[Premier League records and statistics#Points|attain 100 points]] in a single season in the [[2017\u201318 Premier League|2017\u201318]]. Additionally, De Bruyne has been named [[Manchester City#Player of the Year|Manchester City's Player of the Year]], twice, in [[2015\u201316 Manchester City F.C. season|2016]] and [[2017\u201318 Manchester City F.C. season|2018]].\n\nDe Bruyne made his full international debut in 2010, and he has since earned 74 [[Caps (football)|caps]] and scored 19 goals for Belgium. He was a member of the Belgian squads that reached the quarter-finals both at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] and at [[UEFA Euro 2016]]. In 2018 he represented Belgium at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]], winning the [[2018 FIFA World Cup#Third place play-off|third place play-off]] match against [[England national football team|England]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Genk===\nDe Bruyne began his career with hometown club KVV Drongen in 1997. Two years later, he joined [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] and moved to [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in 2005. De Bruyne continued his development in their youth set-up and was rewarded for his progress by being promoted to the first team squad in 2008.\n\nDe Bruyne made his first team debut for [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in a 3\u20130 defeat at [[S. du Pays de Charleroi|Charleroi]] on 9 May 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=Charleroi 3\u20130 Genk|url=http://guardian.touch-line.com/?Lang=0&mTEID=1175&Season=2008%20-%202009&CTID=6&CPID=10&TEID=1175&RFID=&PLID=213148&MAID=408547&ListType=8&pStr=Match_Details&t=2|accessdate=27 May 2011|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011114010/http://guardian.touch-line.com/?Lang=0&mTEID=1175&Season=2008%20-%202009&CTID=6&CPID=10&TEID=1175&RFID=&PLID=213148&MAID=408547&ListType=8&pStr=Match_Details&t=2|archivedate=11 October 2012}}</ref> Having established himself in the team [[2009\u201310 Belgian Pro League|the following season]],<ref name=NFT>{{NFT player|id=39513|name=Kevin De Bruyne|access-date=27 May 2011}}</ref> on 7 February 2010, De Bruyne scored his first goal for the club, which secured all three points for Genk in a 1\u20130 win against [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Genk 1\u20130 Standard Liege|url=http://guardian.touch-line.com/?Lang=0&mTEID=1175&Season=2009%20-%202010&CTID=6&CPID=10&TEID=1175&RFID=&PLID=213148&MAID=419917&ListType=9&pStr=Match_Details&t=3|accessdate=27 May 2011|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011114026/http://guardian.touch-line.com/?Lang=0&mTEID=1175&Season=2009%20-%202010&CTID=6&CPID=10&TEID=1175&RFID=&PLID=213148&MAID=419917&ListType=9&pStr=Match_Details&t=3|archivedate=11 October 2012}}</ref> He scored five goals and made 16 assists in 32 league matches during the 2010\u201311 season as Genk were crowned [[Belgian Pro League|Belgian]] champions for the third time.<ref>{{cite news|title=Genk clinch third Belgian title with Liege draw|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2011/05/17/uk-soccer-belgium-champions-idUKTRE74G7D120110517|work=Reuters|accessdate=27 May 2011|date=17 May 2011}}</ref> On 29 October 2011, De Bruyne scored his first hat-trick for Genk against [[Club Brugge K.V.|Club Brugge]], which ended in a 5\u20134 win for Genk.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin De Bruyne (3) stars as Genk win 5\u20134 at Club Brugge|url=http://www.101greatgoals.com/goals/europe/kevin-de-bruyne-3-stars-as-genk-win-5-4-at-club-brugge/}}</ref> On 28 January 2012, De Bruyne scored a brace against [[Oud-Heverlee Leuven|OH Leuven]] in a 5\u20130 win. On 18 February 2012, De Bruyne scored his first goal back at Genk following his agreed transfer to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and also assisted the other goal in a 1\u20132 away win against [[R.A.E.C. Mons|Mons]]. De Bruyne ended the season by wrapping up the scoring in a 3\u20131 victory over [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]]. He finished the league campaign with eight goals from 28 appearances.\n\n===Chelsea===\n[[File:Kevin De Bruyne Chelsea vs AS-Roma 10AUG2013.jpg|thumb|right|100px|De Bruyne warming up with Chelsea in 2013]]\nOn 31 January 2012, on the winter transfer deadline day, [[Premier League]] club Chelsea and Genk announced the permanent signing of De Bruyne, with the fee rumoured to be in the region of \u00a37 million.<ref>{{cite news| title = Genk confirm De Bruyne sale| url =http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11095/7467271/Genk-confirm-De-Bruyne-sale | publisher = Sky Sport| date = 31 January 2012| accessdate = 31 January 2012 | first = Graeme | last = Bailey}}</ref> He signed a five-and-a-half-year contract at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]], but would stay at Genk for the remainder of the 2011\u201312 season. De Bruyne told the club website, \"To come to a team like Chelsea is a dream but now I have to work hard to achieve the level that's necessary.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Kevin becomes a blue |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/2594667 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130425091338/http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/2594667 |url-status=dead |archive-date=25 April 2013 |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=31 January 2012 |accessdate=7 July 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title = Chelsea sign Kevin De Bruyne from Genk| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/16721393.stm | work = BBC Sport| date = 31 January 2012| accessdate = 31 January 2012}}</ref> On 18 July 2012, De Bruyne made his debut for Chelsea in a friendly match against [[Major League Soccer]] (MLS) side [[Seattle Sounders FC]] in a 4\u20132 win. De Bruyne also played the first half against [[Ligue 1]] giants [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] at [[Yankee Stadium]], [[New York City|New York]].\n\n====Werder Bremen (loan)====\n[[File:Kevin de bruyne werder.JPG|thumb|left|175px|De Bruyne during his spell with Werder Bremen in 2012]]\nOn 31 July 2012, Chelsea announced that De Bruyne was to join [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] in the [[Bundesliga]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/football/2012/jul/31/chelsea-kevin-de-bruyne-werder-bremen</ref> De Bruyne scored his first goal for Bremen in a 3\u20132 defeat to [[Hannover 96]] on 15 September, netting from 11 yards out after being played in by [[Eljero Elia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/346384/gamecast.html |title=Hannover 96 3\u20132 Werder Bremen |publisher=ESPN FC |date=15 September 2012| accessdate = 7 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/264956/report|title=Huszti is hero and villain|publisher=Sky Sports|date=15 September 2012|accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref> De Bruyne continued his good form, scoring in Bremen's next game, a 2\u20132 draw with [[VfB Stuttgart]], on 23 September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/346376/gamecast.html |title=Werder Bremen 2\u20132 VfB Stuttgart |publisher=ESPN FC |date=23 September 2012 | accessdate = 7 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/267321/report|title=Honours even at Weser Stadion|publisher=Sky Sports|date=23 September 2012|accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref> De Bruyne got back on the score sheet on 18 November, scoring the winning goal \u2014 despite his team being down to 10 men \u2014 as Bremen came from a goal down to defeat [[Fortuna D\u00fcsseldorf]] 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/346299/gamecast.html |title= Werder Bremen 2\u20131 Fortuna D\u00fcsseldorf |publisher=ESPN FC |date=18 November 2012 | accessdate = 7 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/279413/report|title=Winning start for Schaaf|publisher=Sky Sports|date=19 November 2012|accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne scored his first goal in over two months on 4 May 2013, since netting a consolation goal in [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]'s 6\u20131 hammering of Bremen, putting his side up 2\u20130 at home to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim]] before a late brace from [[Sven Schipplock]] meant that the game finished 2\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/346123/gamecast.html |title=Werder Bremen 2\u20132 TSG Hoffenheim |publisher=ESPNFC |date=4 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/265457/report|title=Hoffenheim fight back to draw|publisher=Sky Sports|date=4 May 2013|accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref> He followed this up with a goal in Bremen's next match, securing a place in the Bundesliga for the next season with a 1\u20131 draw against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on 11 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/346110/gamecast.htm |title=Werder Bremen 1\u20131 Eintracht Frankfurt |publisher=ESPNFC |date=11 May 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/265466/report|title=Eagles secure a point|publisher=Sky Sports|date=11 May 2013|accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Return to Chelsea====\nAfter a successful loan spell in the Bundesliga with Werder Bremen, De Bruyne was linked with a move to stay in Germany with either [[Borussia Dortmund]] or [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]]. Incoming manager [[Jos\u00e9 Mourinho]], however, assured De Bruyne he was a part of Chelsea's plan for the future, and the player officially returned to Chelsea on 1 July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=De Bruyne to fight for Chelsea place| url=http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/1481782/de-bruyne-fight-chelsea-place?cc=5901|publisher=ESPNFC|date=21 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne injured a knee while scoring his first goal for Chelsea, in a pre-season friendly game against a Malaysia XI,<ref>{{cite news |title=Chelsea: Kevin De Bruyne set for scan on knee injury |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23400115 |first=Richard |last=Conway |website=BBC Sport |date=22 July 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2014}}</ref> but was fit to make his competitive debut on the opening day of the [[2013\u201314 Premier League]] season against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], and made an assist for the first goal in a 2\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/aug/18/chelsea-hull-city-premier-league |title=Jos\u00e9 Mourinho enjoys stylish return as Chelsea cruise against Hull |first=Daniel |last=Taylor |newspaper=The Guardian |date=18 August 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Wolfsburg===\n====2013\u201314 season====\nOn 18 January 2014, [[VfL Wolfsburg|Wolfsburg]] signed De Bruyne for a fee of \u00a318 million (\u20ac22 million).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/jan/18/chelsea-sell-kevin-de-bruyne-wolfsburg |title=Chelsea sell Kevin De Bruyne to Wolfsburg |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=18 January 2014 |accessdate=18 January 2014}}</ref> On 25 January 2014, he made his debut for Wolfsburg in a 3\u20131 home loss against [[Hannover 96]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/wolfsburg/team-news/team-news-de-bruyne-straight-in-for-wolfsburg_132637.html |title=Team News: Kevin de Bruyne straight in for Wolfsburg |work=Sports Mole |date=25 January 2014 |accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref> On 12 April 2014, De Bruyne assisted 2 goals in their 4\u20131 home win against [[1. FC N\u00fcrnberg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whoscored.com/Matches/724028/Live/Germany-Bundesliga-2013-2014-Wolfsburg-Nurnberg |title=Wolfsburg-Nurnberg Live |work=Whoscored.com |date= |accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref> After a week he scored his first goal for Wolfsburg in 3\u20131 away win against [[Hamburger SV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000291918.php |title=De Bruyne: 'We want nine points' &#124; VfL Wolfsburg &#124; Matchday 31 &#124; Reaction \u2013 Bundesliga \u2013 official website |publisher=Bundesliga |date=20 April 2014 |accessdate=7 July 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140422233138/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/liga/news/2013/0000291918.php |archivedate=22 April 2014 |df= }}</ref> He also scored in the last two matches of the [[2013\u201314 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] helping his team to win against [[VfB Stuttgart]] and [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]].\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\n[[File:Emirates Cup - Arsenal v Wolfsburg (20011199918).jpg|thumbnail|De Bruyne playing for Wolfsburg against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in July 2015]]\nDe Bruyne scored his first goal of the [[2014\u201315 VfL Wolfsburg season|2014\u201315 season]] on 2 October 2014, volleying in a clearance from outside the box to salvage a 1\u20131 draw against [[LOSC Lille M\u00e9tropole|Lille]] in the [[2014-15 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2015/matches/round=2000587/match=2014469/postmatch/report/index.html |title=Wolfsburg rally to peg back LOSC |work=UEFA |date=2 October 2014 |accessdate=3 October 2014 }}</ref> In the third group match away to [[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]] on 23 October, De Bruyne scored twice as Wolfsburg secured their first win in the competition with a 4\u20132 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/el/news/2014/0000305024.php |title=De Bruyne Double Fires Wolfsburg to First European Win |work=Bundesliga |date=23 October 2014 |accessdate=23 October 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101165628/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/el/news/2014/0000305024.php |archivedate=1 November 2014 }}</ref> On 30 January 2015, he scored another brace in a 4\u20131 home win against Bayern Munich, their first Bundesliga defeat since April 2014.<ref name=\"VfL Wolfsburg 4 1 Bayern Mun\">{{cite news|last1=Begley|first1=Emlyn|title= VfL Wolfsburg 4\u20131 Bayern Munich|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30991047|accessdate=17 March 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=30 January 2015}}</ref> On 1 March 2015, De Bruyne assisted three goals in a 5\u20133 win over his former club Werder Bremen.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.espn.co.uk/football/sport/match/540771.html|title = Werder Bremen 3\u20135 VfL Wolfsburg|date = 1 March 2015|accessdate = 17 March 2015|work = ESPN (UK)|last = |first = }}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March 2015, De Bruyne scored two goals in a 3\u20131 first-leg Europa League round-of-16 victory over [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2015/matches/round=2000589/match=2014610/postmatch/report/index.html#de+bruyne+unpicks+inter|title = De Bruyne-powered Wolfsburg snap back at Inter|date = 12 March 2015|accessdate = 15 March 2015|website = UEFA.COM|publisher =UEFA |last = |first = }}</ref> On 15 March 2015, he scored one goal and assisted another two in 3\u20130 victory over [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31875612|title = VfL Wolfsburg 3\u20130 Sport-Club Freiburg|date = 15 March 2015|accessdate = 17 March 2015|work = BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne ended the league season with 10 goals and 21 assists, the latter a new [[Bundesliga records#Assists|Bundesliga record]], as Wolfsburg finished second in the [[2014\u201315 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] and qualified for the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtbf.be/sport/football/etranger/allemagne/detail_de-bruyne-entre-dans-l-histoire-de-la-bundesliga?id=8982166|title=De Bruyne entre dans l'histoire de la Bundesliga|language=French|date=16 May 2015|work=RTBF Sport}}</ref> On 30 May 2015, he started and scored in the [[2015 DFB-Pokal Final]] as ''Die W\u00f6lfe'' defeated [[Borussia Dortmund]] 3\u20131 at the [[Olympiastadion (Berlin)|Olympiastadion]] in [[Berlin]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32938029|title=Borussia Dortmd 1\u20133 VfL Wolfsburg|date=30 May 2015|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne ended his breakout season with 16 goals and 27 assists in all competitions,<ref>{{cite web|title='Kevin De Bruyne is off to Man City' says Wolfsburg director Klaus Allofs|url=http://www.espnfc.com/story/2585622/kevin-de-bruyne-is-off-to-manchester-city-says-wolfsburg|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|accessdate=28 August 2015|date=28 August 2015}}</ref> and was named the 2015 [[Footballer of the Year in Germany]].<ref name=Sporza />\n\n====2015\u201316 season====\nDe Bruyne began the season by winning the [[2015 DFL-Supercup]] against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], providing the cross for [[Nicklas Bendtner]]'s 89th-minute equaliser for a 1\u20131 draw and then scoring in the subsequent [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]].<ref name=supercup>{{cite news|last1=Dunbar|first1=Ross|title=Bendtner leads Wolfsburg over Bayern Munich on penalties in German Super Cup clash|url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/bendtner-leads-wolfsburg-over-bayern-munich-on-penalties-in-german-super-cup-clash-080115?vid=null|accessdate=3 August 2015|publisher=Fox Sports|date=1 August 2015}}</ref> On 8 August 2015, he continued his good form by scoring his first goal of the season, and providing two assists in a 4\u20131 win at [[Stuttgarter Kickers]] in the first round of the [[2015\u201316 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=De Bruynes artwork rewarded wide awake Wolves|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2015-16/1/2841065/spielbericht_stuttgarter-kickers-26_vfl-wolfsburg-24.html|publisher=Kicker|accessdate=10 August 2015|date=8 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn August, De Bruyne, in the midst of transfer speculation, insisted that he would not force Wolfsburg to sell him, but admitted that he could not ignore interest from [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], saying: \"If an offer does come, I will hear about it and how much it is, but I have not yet heard anything... I would not go to England just to prove that I can play there. I do not have to go to England... If I go there it\u2019s because for me and for my family it is a good choice. That\u2019s the key for me.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/2892/transfer-zone/2015/08/03/14113752/de-bruyne-i-will-not-force-wolfsburg-to-sell-me |title=Manchester City transfer news: Kevin De Bruyne: I will not force Wolfsburg to sell me |publisher=Goal.com |date=3 August 2015 |accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 August, it was reported that Manchester City had made a second bid for De Bruyne worth \u00a347 million. Wolfsburg sporting director, [[Klaus Allofs]], stated that the club would fight to keep him, saying \"I think some other clubs have definitely turned Kevin\u2019s head... Some huge figures are doing the rounds and I can understand why Kevin is leaving everything open.\"<ref>{{cite news|author=Jackson, Jamie |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/aug/10/kevin-de-bruyne-manchester-city-wolfsburg-47m |title=Manchester City make second bid of \u00a347m for Wolfsburg's Kevin De Bruyne |work=The Guardian |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 August, it was reported that Manchester City had made a bid for De Bruyne worth \u00a358 million. Klaus Allofs said that City had made an \"astonishing\" wage offer to De Bruyne.<ref>{{cite news|title = Kevin de Bruyne: Man City offer 'astonishing' wages |url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34081920 |website=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2015 |accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Manchester City===\n====2015\u201316 season====\n[[File:Kevin De Bruyne (24640482031) (cropped).jpg|thumb|De Bruyne playing for [[Manchester City F.C.|Man City]] in January 2016.|185px]]\nOn 30 August 2015, Manchester City announced the arrival of De Bruyne on a six-year contract, for a reported club-record fee of \u00a355 million (\u20ac75 million), making him the second most expensive transfer in British football history after [[\u00c1ngel Di Mar\u00eda]]'s move to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/Team-news/2015/August/Kevin-De-Bruyne-signs-for-Manchester-City/1440878814 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150831144344/http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/Team-news/2015/August/Kevin-De-Bruyne-signs-for-Manchester-City/1440878814 |url-status=dead |archive-date=31 August 2015 |title=Kevin De Bruyne signs for Manchester City |date=30 August 2015 |accessdate=30 August 2015 |publisher=Manchester City |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title = Man City sign midfielder De Bruyne|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33686731 |website=BBC Sport |date=30 August 2015 |accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref> He made his debut for the team in the Premier League on 12 September against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], replacing injured [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero]] in the 25th minute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Premier League leaders Manchester City continued their 100% start to the season with an injury-time winner over Crystal Palace.|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/34160754|accessdate=14 September 2015|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=12 September 2015}}</ref> On 19 September, he scored his first goal for the club against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in first half stoppage time in an eventual 2\u20131 loss.<ref>{{cite news |author=JJ Bull |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-live-blogs/11874291/Manchester-City-vs-West-Ham-United-live.html |title=Manchester City vs West Ham United: as it happened |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=20 September 2015 |accessdate=20 September 2015}}</ref> He went on to score in a 4\u20131 [[2015\u201316 Football League Cup|League Cup]] win against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], on 22 September<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34253381 |title=Sunderland 1\u20134 Manchester City |website=BBC Sport |date=22 September 2015 |accessdate=23 September 2015}}</ref> and a 4\u20131 loss to [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in the Premier League on 26 September.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/tottenham-hotspur-v-manchester-city-10138638 |title=Recap: Spurs hit four after De Bruyne puts Blues ahead |work=Manchester Evening News |date=26 September 2015 |accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> On 3 October, he scored in the team's 6\u20131 win against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Bevan |first=Chris |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34366600 |title=Manchester City 6\u20131 Newcastle United |website=BBC Sport |date=3 October 2015 |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 October, De Bruyne was announced as one of the players on the longlist for the prestigious [[FIFA Ballon d'Or]] award, alongside such teammates as Sergio Ag\u00fcero and [[Yaya Tour\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/ballon-dor-list-leaked-fifa-10180903 |title=Ballon d'Or shortlist: Eight Manchester-based players in running for award |work=Manchester Evening News |date=2 October 2015 |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> Just 18 days later, on 20 October he was revealed by [[FIFA]] as one of the players on the 23-man shortlist for the Ballon d'Or.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34578624 |title=Ballon d'Or: Ronaldo & Messi joined by Aguero & Toure on list |website=BBC Sport |date=20 October 2015 |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> On 21 October, De Bruyne scored an injury-time winner against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]], to take City within one point of group leaders [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]], with three games remaining.<ref>{{cite news |author=Daniel Taylor |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/oct/21/manchester-city-sevilla-champions-league-match-report |title=Kevin De Bruyne's late strike earns Manchester City victory over Sevilla |work=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> On 1 December, he scored a brace in a 4\u20131 win over [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] to send Manchester City through to the semi-finals of the Football League Cup.<ref>{{cite news |author=Daniel Taylor |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/dec/01/manchester-city-hull-city-capital-one-cup-match-report |title=Kevin De Bruyne hits double as Manchester City send Hull packing |work=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 January 2016, De Bruyne scored a goal in a League Cup semi-final 3\u20131 victory over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], but sustained an injury to his right knee that would keep him out of the team for two months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35425113 |title=Kevin de Bruyne: Man City midfielder set for 10 weeks out|website=BBC Sport |date= |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> On 2 April, De Bruyne made his return from injury in a 4\u20130 win against [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] at [[Dean Court]], scoring the team's second goal in the twelfth minute.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/apr/02/bournemouth-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report|title=Manchester City\u2019s Kevin De Bruyne inspires thrashing of Bournemouth|date=3 April 2016|work=The Guardian}}</ref> Four days later, he scored the opening goal in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] in the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Quarter-finals|UEFA Champions League quarter-final]] first-leg at the [[Parc des Princes]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/04/06/psg-2-man-city-2-fernandinho-and-kevin-de-bruyne-give-city-cause/|title=PSG 2 Man City 2: Fernandinho and Kevin de Bruyne give City cause to dream in Champions League|date=6 April 2016|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref> On 12 April, De Bruyne scored the winning goal against Paris Saint-Germain, advancing Manchester City to the Champions League semi-finals, for the first time in the club's history, on an aggregate score of 3\u20132. Writing in ''[[The Independent]]'', Mark Ogden said, \"It was a stunning goal from the Belgian, who took a touch to control the ball before curling it beyond [[Kevin Trapp]] from the edge of the penalty area.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Mark Ogden |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/manchester-city-vs-psg-match-report-kevin-de-bruyne-stars-as-slick-city-charge-to-semi-final-a6981596.html |title=Manchester City vs PSG match report: Kevin De Bruyne stars as slick City charge to semi-final |work=The Independent |date=12 April 2016 |accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref> De Bruyne's next goal came on 8 May 2016 in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], although the result left City's Champions League qualification hopes out of their own hands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36180831|title=Manchester City 2\u20132 Arsenal|website=BBC Sport|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>[[File:Kevin de Bruyne 2016-12-26 (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|233x233px|De Bruyne during a match against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] on 26 December 2016.]]\n\n====2016\u201317 season====\n{{Quote box\n| quote = \"I think he is a special, outstanding player. He makes everything. Without the ball he is the first fighter, and with the ball he is clear \u2013 he sees absolutely everything.\"\n| source = \u2014[[Pep Guardiola]] on 17 September 2016 describing De Bruyne after his brilliant performances for City<ref name=\"skysports.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/10583036/kevin-de-bruyne-just-behind-lionel-messi-says-manchester-city-manager-pep-guardiola | title=Kevin De Bruyne just behind Lionel Messi, says Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola | publisher=Sky Sports | accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref>\n| align = right\n| width = 33%\n}}\nOn 10 September 2016, De Bruyne scored and assisted in the first [[Manchester derby]] of the [[2016\u201317 Premier League|season]] which City won 2\u20131 and was awarded the ''Man of the Match''.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37263921</ref> On 17 September 2016, De Bruyne was awarded the ''Man of the Match'', in a 4\u20130 win over Bournemouth. De Bruyne scored the first, assisted the fourth, and provided key passes on both the second and third goals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Manchester City v Bournemouth Premier League match report|url=http://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/2016/09/17/city-v-bournemouth-16-september/1474036032274|website=Manchester City|date=17 September 2017|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref> After the international break, Manchester City drew their next game, against Everton, played on 15 October 2016 with the scoreline finishing at 1\u20131. [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero|Ag\u00fcero]] and De Bruyne both missed their penalties while [[Nolito]] came off the bench to equalise for City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37594239|title=Manchester City 1\u20131 Everton|date=15 October 2016|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref> On 1 November, De Bruyne scored from a [[Direct free kick|free kick]] in the team's 3\u20131 win over [[FC Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/11/01/manchester-city-vs-barcelona-live-score-and-goal-updates-from-ch/|title=Manchester City 3 Barcelona 1: Pep Guardiola masterminds City comeback as Gundogan grabs double|first1=Sam|last1=Wallace|first2=J. J.|last2=Bull|date=1 November 2016|publisher=|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref> On 21 January 2017, De Bruyne was involved in both of City's goals, as he netted once himself and also assisted [[Leroy San\u00e9]]'s, in a 2\u20132 home draw with [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]; he was subsequently named ''Man of the Match''.<ref>{{Cite news|last=McNulty|first=Phil|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38620041|title=Manchester City 2\u20132 Tottenham Hotspur|date=12 January 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=19 December 2017|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 19 March 2017, De Bruyne displayed an excellent performance in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium|Etihad Stadium]], where he set up a goal for [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero|Ag\u00fcero]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39246699|title=Manchester City 1\u20131 Liverpool|date=19 March 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=19 December 2017|language=en-GB}}</ref>[[File:Kevin de Bruyne (36243870980).jpg|thumb|258x258px|De Bruyne during a pre-season training session, in July 2017.]]\n\n====2017\u201318 season====\nDe Bruyne set up both [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero|Ag\u00fcero]]'s and [[Gabriel Jesus]]' goals, on 9 September 2017, in a 5\u20130 home victory over [[FC Liverpool|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Yew|first=Oliver|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/man-city-vs-liverpool/373132|title=Manchester City 5\u20130 Liverpool: Jurgen Klopp's side suffer after Sadio Mane's red card|date=9 September 2017|access-date=19 December 2017|language=en|work=SkySports}}</ref> On 16 September, De Bruyne assisted [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero|Ag\u00fcero]] for his first goal in an eventual 6\u20130 win over [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22390|title=Watford v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> On 26 September, De Bruyne scored his first goal of the [[2017\u201318 Manchester City F.C. season|2017\u201318 season]] in a 2\u20130 win over [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41378842|title=Manchester City 2-0 Shakhtar Donetsk|date=26 September 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 30 September 2017, he scored his first goal of the [[2017\u201318 Premier League]] season, as City beat his former club [[Chelsea FC|Chelsea]] with a 1\u20130 scoreline at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]].<ref>{{cite news|last=McNulty|first=Phil|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41370356|title=Chelsea 0\u20131 Manchester City|date=30 September 2017|access-date=19 December 2017|language=en|work=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 14 October, De Bruyne provided two assists in a 7\u20132 win over [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22417|title=Man City v Stoke, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> On 5 November, De Bruyne scored in a 3\u20131 win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22445|title=Man City v Arsenal, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> On 18 November, he scored in a 2\u20130 away win over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22457|title=Leicester v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> On 29 November, he scored City's opener and assisted [[Raheem Sterling|Sterling's]] last-minute winner in a 2\u20131 win over [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22480|title=Man City v Southampton, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 December, De Bruyne scored in a 4\u20130 away win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]], which extended their record run of consecutive top-flight wins to 15 games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22506|title=Swansea v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42247112|title=Swansea City 0-4 Manchester City|date=13 December 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 16 December, he scored in a 4\u20131 win over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], with [[Pep Guardiola]] saying that De Bruyne is \"helping the club become a better institution\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22518|title=Man City v Spurs, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42290590|title=Manchester City 4-1 Tottenham Hotspur|date=16 December 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 27 December, De Bruyne provided an assist for Sterling's goal in a 1\u20130 win over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22538|title=Newcastle v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> On 9 January, De Bruyne scored in a 2\u20131 win over Bristol City in the [[2017\u201318 EFL Cup#Semi-finals|first leg of the semi-finals]] of the [[2017\u201318 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42537815|title=Manchester City 2-1 Bristol City|date=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 20 January, he provided an assist for [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero|Ag\u00fcero's]] first goal of the game (who scored a [[hat-trick]] in the game), in a 3\u20131 win over Newcastle United.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22577|title=Man City v Newcastle, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42672232|title=Manchester City 3-1 Newcastle United|date=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n[[File:Manchester United v Manchester City, 10 December 2017 (20).jpg|left|thumb|252x252px|De Bruyne during the [[Manchester derby]] at [[Old Trafford]], on 10 December 2017, a match City won 2\u20131.]]\nOn 22 January 2018, De Bruyne signed a new long-term contract with the club, keeping him at the club until 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/january/de-bruyne-pens-new-five-year-contract|title=Kevin De Bruyne Pens New Five-Year Contract|date=22 January 2018|accessdate=22 January 2018|publisher=Manchester City|website=mancity.co.uk}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC Sport\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42698924|title=Bristol City 2-3 Manchester City (Agg: 3-5)|date=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 23 January, he scored the winning goal in a 3\u20132 win over Bristol City in the [[2017\u201318 EFL Cup#Semi-finals|EFL Cup semi-final second leg]], which helped City advance to the [[2018 EFL Cup Final|final]], having won the tie by an aggregate scoreline of 5\u20133.<ref name=\"BBC Sport\"/> On 31 January, he scored and assisted in a 3\u20130 win over [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]], and was voted [[BBC Sport|BBC]] ''Man of the Match''.<ref name=\"BBC Sport\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42799045|title=Manchester City 3-0 West Bromwich Albion|date=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 10 February, he provided three assists, two for [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero]] and one for [[Raheem Sterling]], in a 5\u20131 win over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], taking his assists tally to 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22605|title=Man City v Leicester, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42927832|title=Manchester City 5-1 Leicester City|date=10 February 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 25 February, he started in the [[2018 EFL Cup Final]] against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], and played the whole 90 minutes, with Manchester City winning 3\u20130 to obtain their first piece of silverware of the [[2017\u201318 Manchester City F.C. season|2017\u201318 season]], and their first trophy overall under [[Pep Guardiola]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43101681|title=Arsenal 0-3 Manchester City|date=25 February 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March 2018, he provided an assist for [[Gabriel Jesus]] in a 3\u20131 win over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], ensuring that City would require only one more win to secure the [[2017\u201318 Premier League|Premier League title]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22656|title=Everton v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43524315|title=Everton 1-3 Manchester City|date=31 March 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 22 April, he scored in a 5\u20130 win over Swansea City.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22688|title=Man City v Swansea, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> On 13 May, on the final day of the season, De Bruyne assisted [[Gabriel Jesus]]' winning goal in a 1\u20130 win over [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], which took champions City's total points tally to 100. De Bruyne was also voted as [[BBC Sport|BBC]] ''Man of the Match''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22718|title=Southampton v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|website=www.premierleague.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44020180|title=Southampton 0-1 Manchester City|date=13 May 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> For his 16 assists registered across the league season, De Bruyne won the inaugural [[Premier League Playmaker of the Season|Premier League Playmaker of the Season award]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/690283|title=De Bruyne edges Playmaker award|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> He was also selected in the [[PFA Team of the Year (2010s)#Premier League 9|PFA Team of the Year]], and was also voted as [[Manchester City F.C.#Player of the Year|Manchester City Player of the Season]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43810017|title=Manchester City players dominate PFA team of the year|date=18 April 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/may/kevin-de-bruyne-man-city-etihad-player-of-the-season|title=Etihad Player of the Season {{!}} Kevin De Bruyne|work=MCFC|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thepfa.com/thepfa/pfaawards/pfa-premier-league-of-the-year-2018|title=The PFA Premier League Team of the Year|last=ThePFA.com|website=www.thepfa.com|language=en|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422123603/https://www.thepfa.com/thepfa/pfaawards/pfa-premier-league-of-the-year-2018|archive-date=22 April 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n====2018\u201319 season====\nOn 15 August 2018, De Bruyne suffered a knee injury during a training session, with several news websites reporting that he could potentially not play for up to three months.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45200783|title=Kevin de Bruyne: Man City midfielder suffers knee injury in training|date=15 August 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=17 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> Two days later, Manchester City confirmed that he had suffered a lesion of the [[Fibular collateral ligament|lateral collateral ligament]] in his right knee, with no surgery required, and that he was expected to not play for three months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/august/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-update-latest-manchester-city|title=Kevin De Bruyne injury update|website=MCFC|language=en|access-date=17 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45222678|title=Kevin de Bruyne: Manchester City midfielder out for three months|date=17 August 2018 |work=BBC Sport |access-date=17 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11474713/manchester-citys-kevin-de-bruyne-out-for-three-months-with-knee-injury|title=Manchester City's Kevin De Bruyne out for three months with knee injury|work=Sky Sports|access-date=17 August 2018|language=en}}</ref> Soon after De Bruyne returned to action in October 2018, he once again suffered a knee ligament injury in the 4th round of the [[Carabao Cup]] against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. The injury was expected to keep him out for 5\u20136 weeks<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/november/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-news-man-city-latest-update|title=Kevin De Bruyne suffers ligament damage|website=MCFC|language=en|access-date=2018-11-20}}</ref> but he resumed full training much earlier than expected after only 3 weeks out.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/nov/12/kevin-de-bruyne-manchester-city-back-early-injury|title=Kevin De Bruyne set to be back for Manchester City earlier than expected|last=Jackson|first=Jamie|date=2018-11-12|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-11-20}}</ref> He came on as substitute in the [[2018 FA Cup Final|FA Cup final]] against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]], scoring the third goal and assisting two more, as City won the first-ever domestic treble in English men's football.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/may/18/manchester-city-win-treble-watford-fa-cup-final-match-report|title=Manchester City win FA Cup to seal treble with 6-0 demolition of Watford|last=Wembley|first=Daniel Taylor at|date=2019-05-18|work=The Observer|access-date=2019-05-18|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48236232|title=Man City 6-0 Watford: Raheem Sterling scores FA Cup final hat-trick|date=2019-05-18|access-date=2019-05-18|language=en-GB}}</ref> His performances meant he was named ''Man of the Match''.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n====2019\u201320 season====\nOn 15 December 2019, De Bruyne scored a brace in a 3\u20130 [[2019\u201320 Premier League|Premier League]] win over Arsenal at the Emirates.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50702875|title=Manchester City pushed Arsenal deeper into crisis as they won with embarrassing ease at Emirates Stadium.|website=BBC|date=15 December 2019|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne scored his 50th City goal in all competitions on 26 February 2020 in their 2\u20131 come from behind victory over [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] in their Champions League [[2019\u201320_UEFA_Champions_League#Round_of_16|Round of 16]] clash.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport.bt.com/news/manchester-city-fight-back-to-beat-real-madrid-at-bernabeu-S11364433721545|title=Manchester City fight back to beat Real Madrid at Bernabeu|website=BT Sport|date=26 February 2020|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Vincent Kompany Simon Mignolet Kevin De Bruyne vs USA.jpg|thumb|De Bruyne ''(right)'' lining up for Belgium in 2013, alongside [[Vincent Kompany]] and [[Simon Mignolet]].|alt=|256x256px]]\n\nDe Bruyne was capped by [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] at [[Belgium national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Belgium national under-19 football team|under-19]], and [[Belgium national under-21 football team|under-21]] level. He made his debut for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian senior team]] on 11 August 2010 in an international friendly against [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in [[Turku]]; the game ended in a 1\u20130 loss for Belgium.<ref>{{cite web|title=Finland 1\u20130 Belgium|url=http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/football/friendlies/2010/finland-belgium-373758.html|publisher=[[Eurosport]]|accessdate=9 June 2011}}</ref>\n\nBefore making his full debut for Belgium's senior side, De Bruyne was eligible to play for [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]], his mother's birthplace.<ref name=\"fightforchance\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/kevin-de-bruyne-interview-ill-fight-for-chance-at-chelsea-8845258.html|title=Kevin De Bruyne interview: I'll fight for chance at Chelsea...|work=The Independent|accessdate=5 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne became a regular member of Belgium's team during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification - UEFA Group A|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] campaign, where he scored four goals as the Red Devils qualified for their first major tournament in 12 years.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/players/player=358120/news.html|title=Kevin DE BRUYNE|accessdate=22 June 2014|work=FIFA}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May 2014, he was named in Belgium's squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Adnan Januzaj included in Belgium's World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27395150|accessdate=15 May 2014|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=13 May 2014}}</ref> In their first game of the tournament, against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] in [[Belo Horizonte]], De Bruyne assisted [[Marouane Fellaini]]'s equaliser<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chowdhury|first1=Saj|title=Belgium 2\u20131 Algeria|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25285127|accessdate=17 June 2014|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=17 June 2014}}</ref> and was named [[man of the match]] by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=255931/match=300186479/|title=Belgium 2\u20131 Algeria|accessdate=22 June 2014|work=FIFA}}</ref> In the [[2014 FIFA World Cup round of 16|round of 16]], De Bruyne scored Belgium's opening goal in the third minute of [[Overtime#Association football|extra time]] as they defeated the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/27990605|title=Belgium 2\u20131 USA|date=1 July 2014|accessdate=2 July 2014|work=BBC}}</ref>\n[[File:Kevin De Bruyne celebrating Belgium's 2\u20131 win over Brazil.jpg|thumb|256x256px|De Bruyne celebrating Belgium's 2\u20131 win over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], on 6 July 2018.]]\nOn 10 October 2014, De Bruyne scored twice in a 6\u20130 rout of [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying]], equaling the team's record victory in a European qualifier set in 1986.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Brookman|first1=Derek|title=Belgium equal record tally against Andorra|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/qualifiers/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013852/postmatch/report/index.html#belgium+equal+record+tally|accessdate=30 August 2015|publisher=UEFA|date=10 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013852/index.html|title=UEFA EURO 2016 - History - Belgium-Andorra \u2013 UEFA.com|last=uefa.com|date=10 October 2014|work=Uefa.com|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> On 3 September 2015, De Bruyne scored in a 3\u20131 win over Bosnia and Herzegovina.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013973/index.html|title=UEFA EURO 2016 - History - Belgium-Bosnia and Herzegovina \u2013 UEFA.com|last=uefa.com|date=3 September 2015|work=Uefa.com|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> On 10 October 2015, De Bruyne scored in a 4\u20131 win over [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]], which secured Belgium's place at the [[UEFA Euro 2016|UEFA Euro 2016 finals]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/33543987|title=Andorra 1-4 Belgium|date=10 October 2015|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2014042/index.html|title=UEFA EURO 2016 - History - Andorra-Belgium \u2013 UEFA.com|last=uefa.com|date=10 October 2015|work=Uefa.com|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> Three days later, he scored in a 3\u20131 win over [[Israel national football team|Israel]], securing Belgium [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group B|top-spot in the group]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2014068/index.html|title=UEFA EURO 2016 - History - Belgium-Israel \u2013 UEFA.com|last=uefa.com|date=13 October 2015|work=Uefa.com|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref>\nOn 31 May 2016, De Bruyne was selected for Belgium's final 23-man [[UEFA Euro 2016 squads#Belgium|squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/BelRedDevils/status/737693491627720705|title=Belgian Red Devils on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> On 18 June 2016, De Bruyne was praised for his performance in Belgium's 3\u20130 win over the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://squawka.com/en/news/player-ratings-belgium-3-0-republic-of-ireland-de-bruyne-conducts-dominant-win-for-red-devils/700929|title=Player ratings: Belgium 3-0 Republic of Ireland \u2013 De Bruyne conducts dominant win for Red Devils|work=Squawka Football News|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> On 26 June 2016, De Bruyne was voted [[BBC Sport|BBC]] ''Man of the Match'' for his performance in a 4\u20130 win over [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2016#Round of 16|round of sixteen]], where he provided two assists.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36569531|title=Hungary 0-4 Belgium|date=26 June 2016|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne was selected for Belgium's final 23-man [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Belgium|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/belgiums-2018-world-cup-squad-who-joins-hazard-lukaku-23-man/1o481lo2g3q5511q2qts8u7xoy|title=Belgium's 2018 World Cup squad: Who joins Hazard & Lukaku in the 23-man squad? {{!}} Goal.com|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> On 18 June, in the opening game against debutants [[Panama national football team|Panama]], De Bruyne provided an assist for [[Romelu Lukaku]] in an eventual 3\u20130 win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331539/#match-summary|title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia\u2122 - Matches - Belgium - Panama - FIFA.com|last=FIFA.com|website=www.fifa.com|language=en-GB|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44434275|title=World Cup 2018: Belgium beat debutants Panama 3-0 in Sochi|date=18 June 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 6 July, he scored the second goal of the match in a 2\u20131 [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Brazil vs Belgium|quarter-final]] victory over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and was named the [[Player of the match|Man of the Match]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Brazil knocked out of World Cup by Kevin De Bruyne and brilliant Belgium|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jul/06/brazil-belgium-world-cup-quarter-final-match-report|work=The Guardian|accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> In the semi-finals, Belgium were defeated 1\u20130 by eventual champions [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44692297 |title=France 1\u20130 Belgium |website=BBC Sport |author1=Shamoon Hafez |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 }}</ref> On 14 July, Belgium defeated [[England national football team|England]] 2\u20130 in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup#Third place play-off|third-place play-off]].<ref>{{cite news |title=World Cup 2018: England finish fourth after Belgium defeat |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44748604 |accessdate=14 July 2018 |agency=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nConsidered to be a versatile and highly talented player in the media, De Bruyne plays mainly as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central]] or an [[attacking midfielder]] but can also operate in several other positions, and has been used as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[second striker]]; he has even been deployed in a [[Midfielder#Deep-lying playmaker|deeper creative midfield position]], or even in a [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box role]] on occasion. He is often described by pundits as one of the best and most complete modern day [[Playmaker|advanced playmakers]], due to his technique, skill, athleticism, work-rate off the ball, vision, [[Cross (football)|crossing]] accuracy, wide range of passing, and powerful long-range shooting ability with either foot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.squawka.com/news/do-manchester-city-need-kevin-de-bruyne-this-summer/395150|title=Do Manchester City need Kevin De Bruyne this summer?|publisher=Squawka|date=11 June 2015|access-date=16 November 2017|first=Daniel|last=Anwar}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/manchester-city/11833859/Kevin-De-Bruyne-completes-54m-Man-City-transfer.html|title=Kevin De Bruyne completes \u00a354m Man City transfer|work=The Daily Telegraph|author1=Mark Ogden|author2=Mike Whalley|date=30 August 2015|access-date=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/686309 |title=De Bruyne the drive behind Man City success |publisher=Premier League |author1=Adrian Clarke |date=11 May 2018 |accessdate=8 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-perfect-complete-guardiola-conte-reaction-a7976051.html |title=Pep Guardiola and Antonio Conte laud Kevin De Bruyne for being the perfect 'complete' player after masterclass |newspaper=The Independent |author1=Miguel Delaney |date=30 September 2017 |accessdate=8 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsn.ca/de-bruyne-s-versatility-a-key-for-belgium-1.1134678 |title=De Bruyne's versatility a key for Belgium |publisher=TSN |date=9 July 2018 |accessdate=17 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/barclays-premier-league/23/blog/post/2935772/premier-league-disappointing-lack-of-deep-lying-playmakers |title=Disappointing lack of deep-lying playmakers in the Premier League |publisher=ESPN FC |last1=Cox |first1=Michael |date=23 August 2016 |accessdate=24 August 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-de-bruyne-palace-16991871 |title=The attacking dynamic that Kevin De Bruyne will restore for Pep Guardiola |work=The Manchester Evening News |last1=Williams |first1=Josh |date=18 October 2019 |accessdate=6 November 2019 }}</ref>\n\nAlthough he is not blessed with significant physical strength, pace, or ability in the air,<ref name=\"Generazione di Fenomeni\">{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/it/news/3785/generazione-di-fenomeni/2011/11/16/2756464/generazione-di-fenomeni-kevin-de-bruyne-il-gioiello-del-genk-che- |title=Generazione di Fenomeni - Kevin De Bruyne, il gioiello del Genk che il Chelsea sta corteggiando da anni... |publisher=Goal.com |language=Italian |author1=Simone Gambino |date=16 November 2011 |accessdate=17 December 2018 }}</ref> he is a quick and elegant player on the ball, with good [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, while his positional sense, tactical intelligence, movement, direct style of play, and ability to run at defences when in possession also enable him to take advantage of spaces in the opposition's defence, and subsequently create chances and goalscoring opportunities for himself or his teammates, making him a dangerous offensive threat on counter-attacks.<ref name=\"Generazione di Fenomeni\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/premier-league/2017-2018/soccer-de-bruyne-performance-leaves-guardiola-speechless_sto6446741/story.shtml |title=Kevin De Bruyne performance leaves Pep Guardiola speechless |publisher=Eurosport |date=16 December 2017 |accessdate=8 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/09/22/kevin-de-bruyne-is-one-of-best-players-ive-worked-with-says-pep/ |title=Kevin De Bruyne 'is one of best players I've worked with' says Pep Guardiola - but what makes him so special? |newspaper=The Telegraph |author1=JJ Bull |date=22 September 2016 |accessdate=8 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://vivoperlei.calciomercato.com/articolo/dopo-messi-e-cr7-a-chi-il-pallone-doro?referral=vxl_box_mobile |title=Dopo Messi e Cr7 a chi il pallone d'Oro? |publisher=Calciomercato |language=Italian |author1=Ammiraglio Byrd |date=4 October 2016 |accessdate=17 December 2018 }}</ref> In addition to his creative abilities,<ref name=\"Generazione di Fenomeni\" /> he is also capable of scoring goals by making late runs off the ball from behind into the penalty area,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/it/news/14802/uefacom/2016/06/08/24370292/pogba-de-bruyne-e-i-migliori-centrocampisti-di-uefa-euro |title=Pogba, De Bruyne e i migliori centrocampisti di UEFA EURO 2016 |publisher=Goal.com |language=Italian |date=8 June 2016 |accessdate=17 December 2018 }}</ref> and is an accurate [[Direct free kick|set-piece]] taker.<ref name=\"Generazione di Fenomeni\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.sports.yahoo.com/news/goals-assists-set-pieces-stats-172816108.html |title=Goals, assists, set-pieces - The stats that show De Bruyne is almost irreplaceable for City |publisher=Yahoo |date=15 August 2018 |accessdate=17 December 2018 }}</ref> De Bruyne was ranked the fourth-best footballer in the world by ''[[The Guardian]]'' in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2017/dec/19/the-100-best-footballers-in-the-world-2017-interactive|title=The 100 best footballers in the world 2017|date=19 December 2017|work=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=24 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Kevin De Bruyne at Samsung.jpg|thumb|De Bruyne in the Samsung Showroom, during the Red Devils visit.|160px]]\nDe Bruyne's mother is Belgian,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/20/kevin-de-bruyne-stubborn--world-beater|title=Kevin De Bruyne: the stubborn boy who developed into a world beater|first=Kristof|last=Terreur|date=20 October 2017|website=the Guardian|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref> born in [[Burundi]] and has also lived in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/werder-bremen/de-bruyne-es-gibt-keine-chance-fuer-werder-26304510.bild.html|title=Bremens Belgier ist im Sommer weg: De Bruyne: \"Es gibt keine Chance f\u00fcr Werder!\"|trans-title=Bremen's Belgian going to leave in summer: De Bruyne:\"There is no chance for Werder!\"|language=German|newspaper=[[Bild]]|date=20 September 2012|accessdate=12 April 2015}}</ref> His hometown [[Drongen]], a submunicipality of the city of [[Ghent]], is situated in [[Flanders]], the Dutch-speaking part of Belgium.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mcfcwatch.com/2018/03/20/pep-guardiola-to-make-surprise-visit-to-belgium-on-june-2nd-report/|title=Pep Guardiola to make surprise visit to Belgium on June 2nd \u2013 report \u2013 City Watch|access-date=10 May 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://staantribune.nl/een-jongen-uit-drongen-hoe-het-begon-voor-kevin-de-bruyne/|title=Kevin De Bruyne: een jongen uit Drongen|date=29 September 2017|work=Staantribune|access-date=10 May 2018|language=nl-NL}}</ref> Aside from his mother tongue [[Dutch language|Dutch]], De Bruyne also speaks [[French language|French]], [[English language|English]] and [[German language|German]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://premierskillsenglish.britishcouncil.org/players/player-week/kevin-de-bruyne|title=Kevin De Bruyne|website=premierskillsenglish.britishcouncil.org|language=en|access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I3z_4jZR-ek|title=Kevin de Bruyne im DAZN Interview vor Schalke vs Manchester City|publisher=DAZN_DE on Youtube|date=20 February 2019|accessdate=29 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nSince 2014, De Bruyne has been in a relationship with Mich\u00e8le Lacroix,<ref>{{cite web|last=Newman |first=Benjamin |url=http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/michele-lacroix-new-blonde-girlfriend-of-chelseas-de-bruyne-has-posted-pictures-of-the-couple-on-facebook/ |title=Mich\u00e8le Lacroix, new blonde girlfriend of Chelsea\u2019s De Bruyne, has posted pictures of the couple on Facebook |publisher=101 Great Goals |date=3 January 2014 |accessdate=22 March 2015}}</ref> who announced on 28 September 2015 that she was pregnant with the couple's son.<ref>{{cite web|last=Newman |first=Benjamin |url=http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/social/michele-lacroix-girlfriend-of-man-citys-kevin-de-bruyne-announces-shes-pregnant-with-a-boy-instagram/ |title=Mich\u00e8le Lacroix, girlfriend of Man City's Kevin De Bruyne, announces she's pregnant with a boy |publisher=101 great goals |date=28 September 2015 |accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> Mason Milian De Bruyne was born on 10 March 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtbf.be/sport/football/etranger/angleterre/detail_kevin-de-bruyne-heureux-papa-d-un-petit-mason-milian?id=9236863 |title=Kevin De Bruyne heureux papa d'un petit Mason Milian |publisher=Rtbf.be |date= |accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref> Their second son, Rome De Bruyne, was born on 31 October 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pulse.ng/sports/football/de-bruyne-welcomes-2nd-child-with-partner-michele/1bgwv6t |title=De Bruyne welcomes 2nd child with partner Michele |website=pulse.ng |date= 31 October 2018 |accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref> De Bruyne and Lacroix married in June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/625362/stunning-blonde-wag-michele-lacroix-marries-manchester-city-star-kevin-de-bryune |title=Meet the stunning blonde WAG married to Manchester City star |website=dailystar.co.uk |publisher=DailyStar |date= 27 June 2017 |accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis autobiography, entitled ''Keep It Simple'', was published by Borgerhoff & Lamberigts in October 2014.<ref name=northcroft>{{cite news |author=Jonathan Northcroft |title=City Whizzkid |newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=25 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nDe Bruyne was an ambassador for the 2014 [[Special Olympics]], which took place in [[Antwerp]] and was involved in a controversial advertisement campaign, via his personal [[Instagram]] account. Employing the slogan (in [[Dutch language|Dutch]]): \"Would you still be my fan if I looked like this?\", De Bruyne was depicted resembling a person with [[Down syndrome]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccerly.com/article/dflores/kevin-de-bruynes-controversial-special-olympics-campaign|title=Kevin de Bruyne's controversial Special Olympics campaign|first=David Flores -|last=dflores|website=Soccerly|accessdate=16 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 1 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2| Club\n!rowspan=2| Season\n!colspan=3| League{{efn|Includes [[Belgian Pro League]] Europa League and Championship playoffs}}\n!colspan=2| National Cup{{efn|Includes [[Belgian Cup]], [[DFB-Pokal]], [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2| League Cup{{efn|Includes [[EFL Cup|League/EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2| Europe\n!colspan=2| Other\n!colspan=2| Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=5| [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]\n| [[2008\u201309 Belgian First Division|2008\u201309]]<ref name=SW/>\n| [[Belgian First Division]]\n|2||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n| [[2009\u201310 Belgian Pro League|2009\u201310]]<ref name=SW/>\n| [[Belgian Pro League]]\n|35||3||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||2{{efn|name=UEL|Appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||0||1{{efn|name=BSC|Appearance in [[Belgian Super Cup]]}}||0||40||3\n|-\n| [[2010\u201311 Belgian Pro League|2010\u201311]]<ref name=SW/>\n| Belgian Pro League\n|32||5||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||3{{efn|name=UEL}}||1||0||0||35||6\n|-\n| [[2011\u201312 Belgian Pro League|2011\u201312]]<ref name=SW/>\n| Belgian Pro League\n|28||8||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||6{{efn|name=UCL|Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||1{{efn|name=BSC}}||0||36||8\n|-\n!colspan=2| Total\n!97!!16!!3!!0!!colspan=2|\u2014!!11!!1!!2!!0!!113!!17\n|-\n| [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] (loan)\n| [[2012\u201313 SV Werder Bremen season|2012\u201313]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin De Bruyne|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/2012-13/59516/vereinsspieler_de-bruyne-kevin.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=17 August 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n| [[Bundesliga]]\n|33||10||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||34||10\n|-\n| [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n| [[2013\u201314 Chelsea F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=SW/>\n| [[Premier League]]\n|3||0||0||0||3||0||3{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||9||0\n|-\n| rowspan=4| [[VfL Wolfsburg|Wolfsburg]]\n| [[2013\u201314 VfL Wolfsburg season|2013\u201314]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin De Bruyne|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/2013-14/59516/vereinsspieler_de-bruyne-kevin.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=17 August 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n| Bundesliga\n|16||3||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||18||3\n|-\n| [[2014\u201315 VfL Wolfsburg season|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin De Bruyne|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/2014-15/59516/vereinsspieler_de-bruyne-kevin.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=17 August 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n| Bundesliga\n|34||10||6||1||colspan=2|\u2014||11{{efn|name=UEL}}||5||colspan=2|\u2014||51||16\n|-\n| [[2015\u201316 VfL Wolfsburg season|2015\u201