tegory:Northwestern University alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{About|the voice actress|others|Jennifer Taylor (disambiguation){{!}}Jennifer Taylor}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jen Taylor\n| image              = Jen Taylor.jpg\n| caption            = Jen Taylor in 2007\n| birth_name         = Jennifer Lee Taylor\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1973|2|17}}<ref>{{cite tweet|user=jentaylorfortown | first=Jen | last=Taylor | number= 832737204468211712|title=Thank you for my happy birthday wishes, friends! It has been relaxing and full of cheese which explains this photo. | date=February 17, 2017 | access-date=March 22, 2017 }}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Seattle]], Washington, U.S.\n| occupation         = Actress, voice actress\n| alias              = \n| yearsactive        = 1993\u2013present\n}}\n'''Jennifer Lee Taylor''' (born February 17, 1973) is an American actress and voice actress best known for her roles as [[Cortana (Halo)|Cortana]] in various [[Halo (series)|''Halo'' games]] as well as the [[Cortana|intelligent personal assistant]] of the same name. She also voices Zoey in ''[[Left 4 Dead]]''; [[Princess Peach]], [[Toad (Nintendo)|Toad]], and [[Toadette]] in various [[Mario (franchise)|''Mario'' games]] between 1999 and 2008;<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://southtexasgamersexpo.com/jen-taylor/|title=Jen Taylor - South Texas Gamers Expo|date=August 19, 2016|newspaper=South Texas Gamers Expo|language=en-US|access-date=January 15, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116170458/http://southtexasgamersexpo.com/jen-taylor/|archive-date=January 16, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Salem in ''[[RWBY]]'', and Lina, Windranger, Puck and Medusa in ''[[Dota 2]]''.\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Live action ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable